Pelehonuamea
Goddess of Fire and Volcanoes
 After the pandemic hit and stimulus checks were sent out by the government, I made the decision to visit the Big Island of Hawaii thinking I’ll never get the chance again in my lifetime. The duration of my visit was for two weeks but the impact left a memory of a lifetime. The ocean, the flora, and the camaraderie of the community I felt on the sacred land restored a sense of peace within me which led my heart back into painting and that of Pele, who I relate to in more ways than one when it comes to her story and her rage. Pele taught me how to breathe deeply, again. 

Slide 2: 

Ego Death
Self portrait in the Atlantic Ocean, after overdosing on psilocybin 
After Bernie Sanders withdrew from the 2020 elections when the establishment candidates of the Democratic Party coalized against him, like many people involved in the progressive movement, I felt a sense of loss and direction given that this was the second time around of facing disappointment and a harsh understanding of how deeply corrupted the system is in this country. Having dealt with months of isolation during the pandemic, I was offered a trip to Miami and put trust in someone I considered a friend who had me ingest more than the amount of shrooms my body could handle. It put me over the edge to the point where I almost drowned in the Atlantic Ocean. In the moment when I felt like I was transcending into another realm, I was sent back to Earth and waves washed me up ashore. I haven’t served my purpose yet, and I have come to believe my purpose lies in storytelling through my art. 

#artivism #queensartist #newyorkartist
#hawAii #pele  #Pelehonuamea. #bigisland 

#ego #egodeath #psilocybin #storytelling

Dear Portraits Supporters: We extended Portraits of the Revolution through this evening, December 1, and thereafter the Portraits of the Revolution exhibition will exist as an online gallery to continue to magnify the urgent need of policy changes to address the overwhelming social and political injustices which cripple American society. We will announce the launch and url when it's live!

I am very grateful to Sneha for bringing this beautiful show to the gallery. I'm proud that EV Gallery has had the privilege of showing several pointed activism art shows by deeply passionate artists. 

Slide 1: 

Bernie Sanders
Vermont Senator, Former Presidential Candidate, Activist
"The change begins when we say to the billionaire class: “You can’t have it all. You can’t get huge tax breaks while children in this country go hungry. You can’t continue sending our jobs to China while millions are looking for work. You can’t hide your profits in the Cayman Islands and other tax havens, while there are massive unmet needs in every corner of this nation. Your greed has got to end. You cannot take advantage of all the benefits of America if you refuse to accept your responsibilities as Americans.” 

Slide 2:

Dannelly Rodriguez
Movement Lawyer, Housing Rights Activist, Community Organizer
“Saying we need to unfuck the world implies that the world is fucked. It begs the question, why is the world fucked? It’s fucked because it prioritizes profit over people, white supremacy, and rich people over poor people. All of these factors are deeply ingrained within and are essential to capitalism. Capitalism is racism, classism and patriarchy. So in order to unfuck the world we need to center people, black people, brown people, poor people and women and gender non conforming people. We need power. All power to the people.”

#berniesanders #dannellyrodriguez #powertothepeople

My family and I are always asked where we are from and Northeast India is never on the list of their guesses. I don't blame people for not knowing the existence of Bishnupriya Manipuris since our history is a bit tainted while we consider ourselves as the Indigenous people of Assam. When we migrated to the States, our identities and the languages we spoke faded as we assimilated into the American culture. 
-
My family has inspired me to work on the next set of creations that will reflect where I come from and in due time, I will return home once again. 

❤️

With prayer in my heart, stepped foot on familiar land and this time around reached Mauna Kea, which is 13,803 ft above sea level with only 40% oxygen. To watch the sunset and then, star gaze and see both Polaris star and Sirius (south star) at the same time, I can only describe in a few words how healed I felt. I am now working on an e-book of my visit to the Big Island and showcase the love I have for this land that teaches me how to breathe and renew my perspective of life itself. 

mahalo mauna kea a me nā kānaka

This is the story of #RayanSuleiman a 7 year old Palestinian child who died of fear while being chased by IDF soldiers in the occupied West Bank. Cause of death was heart failure due to intense fear. Artist @snaybelle gifted me with this painting and all she said was to donate to the cause. I kept it and loved the painting for a couple of days until I gifted it to my dearest Palestinian friend in NY who fell in love with it. May he rest in peace 🪽 #freepalestine #restinpower #gaza #art #palestinewillbefree #sadness #grief #westgaza #israelisaterrorstate #IDF
